questions.question:
Consider the following ANSI C program.

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int arr[4][5];
    int i, j;
    for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
        for (j = 0; j < 5; j++) {
            arr[i][j] = 10 * i + j;
        }
    }
    printf("%d\n", arr[i+j][j+i]);
    return 0;
}

What is the output of the above program?

A. 14
B. 20
C. 24
D. 30
